	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Yaxa,<br />
<br />
Being able to port to a zone that is 1-2 zones away from the hunting spot might seem all there is that is needed in EQ, but once you play WoW (I don't know if you did) you'll find that the flow of getting started is much more convenient.<br />
<br />
In WoW the zones are setup such that I can camp at a near town the night before.  I log in the next day with some friends, we quickly can cross invite each other across zones (this is needed!!!) without seeing each other.  While running to the spot we want to be, we can do all our buffs because you can run and cast a lot of these spells.  The mana regen occurs so quick that when we arrive, even if someone in the group isn't ready, someone can start clearing/killing.<br />
<br />
Now, I understand that EQ might have gotten faster, it's far from this speed.  After a cleric buffs a whole group with conviction, and the chanter buffs everyone with haste and clairvoyance, etc. there is some major downtime where you wait till you get full or some portion of mana to get you started.  Class dependency will require you to wait in many more situations because the tank can't solo the mob without the presence of the other people in the group.  <br />
<br />
Travelling to the desired hunting area is a lot more difficult in EQ as well and it's a lot more dangerous too... somtimes rediculously so, which results in taking even more time.  Some danger is ok, but anything like the pre-Barindu ports where you need to get a cleric there praying invis doesn't drop is pure frustration and time consuming.<br />
<br />
The lack of zoning for the most part in WoW keeps things fast paced as opposed to EQ waiting several seconds to enter a new zone.<br />
<br />
Corpse runs are a good example of getting back into action quick.  Now I wish there was more penalty for dying in WoW cuz it's just plain trivial, but geeze, does the penalty have to be 10 min of medding to get buffs on everyone, just so we can wait another 10 min to med again before we restart our group?!  And this is coming from someone who had 2 SKs casting Zevfeer's bites on eyes to get mana going as fast as possible.<br />
<br />
So cutting down on some of those annoying features EQ has, but not necessarily make it WoW exactly, would be a big plus.  I've heard it many times before that in WoW people feel they can accomplish something in an hour.  Most of that hour is prep-time in EQ.  <br />
<br />
One last thing...I really like how there are several towns in WoW where you will find people camping out at.  You do not find this in EQ anymore.  In old world EQ and up to velious this was consistent.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
