		<!-- message -->
		<div>Locked Encounters seems lame to me.  I can appreciate the benefits of having instanced content available, but you need to have <i>some</i> gameworld where the risk variables are both the content itself <i>and</i> other players engaging that content.<br />
<br />
I mean, if you don't want training to be a problem just adjust faction for mobs in the zone so they don't assist each other, or aren't immediately aggressive to players.<br />
<br />
Sounds pretty boring me to me, however.  They have already made faction meaningless in a number of other ways.<br />
<br />
I haven't played WoW or EQ2 to provide any insight in regards to their innovative (or not so innovative) design, but the idea of faster recovery during times of inactivity is appealing to me.  Meditation and HP regeneration when sitting are outdated by being a fixed rate, they should be a percentage so that all characters have an equal amount of downtime required to go from badly injured or OoM to being fully recovered and ready to continue.  The Guild Hall pool is handy, but it repeats the same error of the past by simply being a fixed rate &quot;buff&quot; type effect which expediates recovery.  Also, the pool is only available when you are far removed from action, and in solitude exclusively with your guildmates.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
